# HDTV Backend Rules

- Python 3.11, FastAPI strictly async
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 Async + Alembic for migrations
- Use `httpx` for HTTP (never `requests`)
- LLM calls ONLY via `LLM_BASE_URL` HTTP — never embed model in FastAPI
- Celery for ReAct agent loops; API returns 202 Accepted
- Every tool call MUST log to `ai_audit_logs` table
- Structure: `routers/` → `services/` → `models/` — no business logic in routers
- Config via Pydantic `BaseSettings` + `.env` — no hardcoded IPs/keys
- Strict type hints on all functions
- Docker: alpine-based Python images, memory limits in compose
